data.title: Core Scientific shareholders to vote on CoreWeave merger. CoreWeave stock surged 140% in 2025. Voting amid fall.
data.description: Shareholders of Core Scientific are set to vote on the proposed merger with CoreWeave on Thursday morning. CoreWeave stock has surged by 140% in 2025. The vote comes as CoreWeave stock experiences a decline. Investors are closely monitoring this merger as it unfolds.

data.title: Insmed stock surged, Argenx rose moderately after beating third-quarter calls. Biotech companies on the rise.
data.description: Insmed's stock experienced a significant surge in early trading on Thursday, while Argenx saw a more moderate rise. Both top biotech companies exceeded expectations for the third quarter. Insmed's stock performance was particularly notable, showing a sharp increase compared to Argenx. News reports were optimistic about the performance of both companies, with Insmed leading the way and Argenx following closely behind. This update was widely covered in investor circles, showcasing the positive momentum and growth of both companies in the biotech sector.

data.title: Biogen's stock drops due to profit cut for 2025, moves back into buy zone..cells expected tax charge.
data.description: Biogen's shares experienced a decline on Thursday following the company's decision to revise its 2025 profit forecast due to an anticipated tax charge. The company's stock dropped, placing it back in a favorable buying range. This development was reported by Investor's Business Daily.

data.title: Eli Lilly surpasses Q3 expectations with stock jump, driven by Mounjaro and Zepbound.
data.description: Shares of Eli Lilly surged on Thursday morning following the company's impressive performance in the third quarter, where they exceeded expectations with their top two drugs, Mounjaro and Zepbound. The drugmaker's stock saw a significant increase after the positive results were revealed, showcasing their strong financial standing. This successful outcome in the third quarter emphasized the company's growth potential and solid position in the market.

data.title: Alnylam stock doubled in 2025 but dropped on earnings due to US govt subpoena related to four drugs.
data.description: Shares of Alnylam Pharmaceuticals experienced a decline in value on Thursday following the announcement of a subpoena from the U.S. government regarding its four medications. Despite this setback, the company's stock had previously doubled in 2025. This news was reported by Investor's Business Daily.

data.title: Fed's 25-point rate cut raises employment worries per Powell. End of QE.
data.description: Jerome Powell announced that the Federal Reserve has cut rates by 25 basis points due to worries about employment risks. This measure also signifies the conclusion of quantitative easing.

data.title: Plymouth Scholars Charter Academy in Michigan named 2025 Blue Ribbon School by Michigan Department of Education.
data.description: In Plymouth, Michigan on October 30, 2025, Plymouth Scholars Charter Academy, a partner-school of National Heritage Academies (NHA), was designated a 2025 Michigan Blue Ribbon School by the Michigan Department of Education. This recognition highlights the successful collaboration between parents and the school community leading to academic excellence.

data.title: Guide explains how to calculate car's total loss value - insurers declare total loss if repair costs reach 70-80% of value.
data.description: In Tampa, Florida on October 30, 2025, a guide provided by USInsuranceAgents.com details the process for determining a vehicle's total loss value. Insurance companies typically consider a car a total loss if the cost of repairs amounts to 70% to 80% or more of the vehicle's total value. This guideline assists vehicle owners in understanding when their car may be declared a total loss by insurers.

data.title: energyRe secures $370 million for South Carolina solar portfolio with global lenders, emphasizes affordable energy.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, energyRe, a prominent energy developer in the United States, achieved financial close on a project emphasizing their commitment to providing dependable and cost-effective energy solutions to address the increasing energy needs of America. Based in Charleston, S.C., energyRe's successful financial close reaffirms their role in the industry, showcasing their ability to deliver reliable energy projects. This achievement highlights their leadership in delivering affordable energy solutions to meet the growing demand in the country.

data.title: PlanSource is named UKG 2025 Innovator of the Year for revolutionizing benefits administration | Leading connected benefits experiences.
data.description: PlanSource, a prominent benefits administration technology and services company based in Orlando, Florida, was recently honored by UKG as the 2025 Innovator of the Year within the UKG Partner Network. This recognition highlights PlanSource's dedication to streamlining benefits administration and enhancing the employee benefits journey through innovative automation, extensive integrations, and cutting-edge technologies. The award underscores PlanSource's position as a leader in the industry.

data.title: Litify introduces AI-powered Damages Assistant to aid law firms with medical record analysis.(Group: Litify, Partner: Supio)
data.description: Litify, a comprehensive legal platform for top-performing legal professionals, unveiled LitifyAI Damages Assistant in New York. This latest feature, developed in partnership with Supio, a prominent legal AI platform specializing in personal injury law, streamlines the compilation of medical record chronologies and reconciliation for plaintiff law firms. The collaboration aims to assist law firms in identifying lucrative prospects in intricate medical records and offers automated solutions.

data.title: Advisor360° offers enterprise-grade wealth management tech to RIAs at Schwab IMPACT 2025 with free tech assessments.
data.description: A company based in Needham, Massachusetts is providing free technology assessments to Registered Investment Advisors (RIAs) to assist them in transforming their disjointed technology systems into cohesive and strategic tools. Advisor360°'s initiative aims to help RIAs enhance their operational efficiency and decision-making capabilities by offering complimentary assessments. This opportunity enables RIAs to harness the power of integrated technology solutions.

data.title: Andersen Consulting strengthens platform with Collaboration Agreement with threon for enhanced transformation capabilities.
data.description: In San Francisco, it was announced that Andersen Consulting has strengthened its business transformation and digital transformation capabilities by entering into a Collaboration Agreement with threon. This move is significant as it enhances Andersen Consulting's expertise in these areas, allowing it to better serve its clients. The agreement is expected to bring together the strengths of both companies in order to offer more comprehensive solutions. This partnership signifies a key strategic move for Andersen Consulting and demonstrates its commitment to enhancing its services.

data.title: MSCI starting public offering of senior unsecured notes in NYSE (ticker: MSCI). Funds will be used for general corporate purposes.
data.description: In New York, MSCI Inc. (NYSE: MSCI), a key provider of decision support tools for investors globally, has begun an offering of senior unsecured notes. The Offering is a registered public offering and is contingent on market conditions. The company plans to utilize the net proceeds for general corporate needs, which could involve potential repayments.

data.title: China's rare earth export restrictions for defense firms raised before trade truce. Stock prices surged.
data.description: Prior to the recent escalation, China had already halted rare earth exports to defense companies. The trade truce between Trump and Xi raised concerns, leading to a rise in rare earth stocks.

data.title: Black Girl Vitamins launches Her Balance, a transformative vaginal probiotic for Black women's health. More details on PRNewswire.
data.description: Chicago-based company Black Girl Vitamins has recently launched Her Balance, a new vaginal probiotic aimed at promoting vaginal health. The product is backed by extensive research and community feedback and seeks to provide compassionate care and culturally relevant support. Founded in 2025, Her Balance is specially formulated to support women's health and well-being.
